hr.br:
UPDATED 3/25/2020 4:00 pm
As per Minnesota Governor's announcement on Wednesday, March 26, regarding MN Public School Closures and COVID-19,
JCC Schools will be closed from Monday, March 30 through Monday, May 4. During this time, a Distance Learning Plan will be implemented. Please click on link above for all information regarding distance learning.

span.style: font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial;

p.span: During our Distance Learning, we will continue with scheduled school breaks. For instance, our spring break will still be April 9-13. There will be no school attendance/check ins required for Thursday, April 9, Friday, April 10, or Monday, April 13. Students are still able and welcome to work on assignments. Daycare and food service will not be available April 9-13.

span.style: font-size: 18px;
font-size: 18px;

hr.p:
Facilities:
--All JCC School Buildings and Facilities are closed to the public until further notice.
--The Indoor Pool is closed to the public until further notice.
--The Fitness Center and Walking Track are closed to the public until further notice.
Food Service:
last updated March 16th @ 3:15 pm
last updated March 25th @ 4:00 pm
Effective Wednesday, March 18 JCC Food Service will provide student meals (breakfast/lunch) "drive-up" style for any students 18 and under. If you arrive by car, stay in your car and food service staff will come out to you. if you arrive on foot, start lining up at the selected spot. Stay 6 feet away from the person in front of you. Stay in line. Food service staff will call you forward to deliver the meals. You can pick up for your own household. Please stay home if you have a fever, cough or shortness of breath. Also, wash your hands before and after you pick up your meals.

Buses transport students to the Middle School from the upper North parking lot at the High School in the morning at 7:45am and return to the upper north lot at the high school at 3:20 pm and Riverside at 3:25 pm where students can switch to their regular bus routes.
The late bus will pick up at the Middle School at 5:15 pm and deliver students to Riverside (West doors) at 5:35pm or the High School (lower South lot) and then route back to Lakefield (Middle School).
Please contact Palmer Bus Service for any questions on times or routes at 507 849 7117 or 507 841 2458.
